<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[128,654,583,1754]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
DIAGNOSIS: Eye hairs sparsely present and prominent over the entire surface of the eyes. Mesonotum sits more deeply into the pronotum than in other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier in de Saussure" authorityYear="1854" box="[341,419,672,696]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Apoica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[341,419,672,696]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Apoica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[435,534,671,695]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="19.[112,150,1679,1701]" captionTargetBox="[88,1187,1282,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-110@19.[88,1188,1282,1644]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Fig. 20. A: Apoica ellenae. Mesonotum sits lower relative to pronotum, mesonotal bristles do not reach anterior margin; B: Apoica thoracica. Mesonotum sits higher (typical), mesonotal bristles reach anterior margin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5387632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5387632/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">fig. 20A</figureCitation>
). Pronotal fovea recessed into a pit. Metanotal bristles curved; mesonotal bristles not reaching anterior margin; mesonotum, metanotum, and dorsal metasoma covered with fine, silverygrey pubescence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[128,654,583,1754]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
DESCRIPTION: Wing length 15.0 mm. 
<emphasis box="[567,627,848,872]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Color</emphasis>
— Brown cuticle with silvery-grey ‘‘frosting’’ (especially the dorsal metasoma) due to fine pubescence. Two short pale longitudinal mesonotal marks appear medial to parapsidial furrows, but not reaching anterior or posterior border of the mesonotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
